<?xml version="1.0"?><?mso-application progid="Excel.Sheet"?><Workbook xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:spreadsheet" xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:x="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel" xmlns:ss="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:spreadsheet" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><DocumentProperties xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office"><LastAuthor>Djurre van Dijk</LastAuthor><LastSaved>2018-11-09T16:25:17Z</LastSaved><Version>16.00</Version></DocumentProperties><OfficeDocumentSettings xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office"><AllowPNG/></OfficeDocumentSettings><ExcelWorkbook xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel"><WindowHeight>9750</WindowHeight><WindowWidth>13170</WindowWidth><WindowTopX>32767</WindowTopX><WindowTopY>32767</WindowTopY><ProtectStructure>False</ProtectStructure><ProtectWindows>False</ProtectWindows></ExcelWorkbook><Styles><Style ss:ID="Default" ss:Name="Normal"><Alignment ss:Vertical="Bottom"/><Borders/><Font ss:FontName="Calibri" x:Family="Swiss" ss:Size="11" ss:Color="#000000"/><Interior/><NumberFormat/><Protection/></Style><Style ss:ID="s62"><Alignment ss:Vertical="Top" ss:WrapText="1"/></Style></Styles><Worksheet ss:Name="Script"><Table x:FullColumns="1" x:FullRows="1" ss:StyleID="s62" ss:DefaultColumnWidth="51.75" ss:DefaultRowHeight="15"><Column ss:StyleID="s62" ss:Width="126.75"/><Column ss:StyleID="s62" ss:Width="107.25"/><Column ss:StyleID="s62" ss:Width="290.25"/><Column ss:StyleID="s62" ss:Width="147.75"/><Column ss:StyleID="s62" ss:Width="297"/><Column ss:StyleID="s62" ss:Width="120"/><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0" ss:Height="60"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">UNIT_UPGRADES_UNIQUE</Data></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">The DEV TEAM / MISC NOTES column contains info on what text between { } signs means (if applicable). It usually stands for either a numeric value, or a numeric value with an icon. Text between [ ] signs stands for a certain type of icon. </Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">SCENE ID</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">TEXT ID</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ENGLISH STRING</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">LOCALIZED STRING</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ALTERNATIVE ENGLISH STRING</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ALTERNATIVE LOCALIZED STRING</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">LOCALIZATION NOTES</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">DEV TEAM / MISC NOTES</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">PLAGUED_QUILL_SHOT</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_NAME</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Plagued Quill Shot</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Wystrzelenie pióra zarazy</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">PLAGUED_QUILL_SHOT</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_DESCRIPTION</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Shoot Xenoplague-infected serrated quills at the target.</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Ostrzeliwuje cel ząbkowanymi piórami zakażonymi zarazą.</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">PLAGUED_QUILLS</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_NAME</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Plagued Quills</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Pióra zarazy</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0" ss:Height="75"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">PLAGUED_QUILLS</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_DESCRIPTION</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">This unit is covered in serrated quills. Each time it takes damage, it expels Plagued Quills, dealing {QuillsDamage}[damagephysical/] with {Quillsinfection}[strengthbio/] to cause [abilityred]Parasitic Infection[/abilityred] to adjacent enemy units.</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Ta jednostka jest pokryta ząbkowanymi piórami. Za każdym razem, gdy otrzymuje obrażenia, wystrzeliwuje pióra zarazy, zadające {QuillsDamage}[damagephysical/] z {Quillsinfection}[strengthbio/] i powodujące [abilityred]infekcję pasożytniczą[/abilityred] u sąsiadujących jednostek wroga.</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">BLESSING_OF_ARTOK</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_NAME</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Blessing of Artok</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Błogosławieństwo Artoka</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">BLESSING_OF_ARTOK</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_DESCRIPTION</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">As long as the Hand that Gives is alive the Hand that Takes is healed for {Healing}[HP/] at the start of each turn.</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Dopóki ręka, która daje, pozostaje przy życiu, dopóty ręka, która odbiera, odzyskuje {Healing}[HP/] na początku każdej tury.</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">THE_ESTEQ_TITHE</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_NAME</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">The Es'Teq Tithe</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Dziesięcina dla Es’Tequ</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">THE_ESTEQ_TITHE</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_DESCRIPTION</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">All enemies have an {Drainstrength}[strengthentropy/] chance to suffer [abilityred]Essence Drain[/abilityred], this unit gains essence for each enemy drained.</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Wszyscy wrogowie mają szansę {Drainstrength}[strengthentropy/] na doznanie [abilityred]wyssania esencji[/abilityred]. Ta jednostka zyskuje esencję za każdego wyzyskanego wroga.</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ESTEQ</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">TEMPLATE_NAME</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Es'Teq</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Es’Teq</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">In the text below, any inserted strings - anything of the form {text} - is replaced by an integer value for the thing described in the brackets. If the {text} is not followed by a unit - e.g. shields, hitpoints - the icon for the unit is inserted together with the integer. The same holds for symbols - e.g. '+', '%' - which are occasionally inserted together with the integer.</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">For references to game terminology and in-world references, please check the glossary delivered as part of the documentation.</Data></Cell></Row></Table><WorksheetOptions xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel"><Unsynced/><Selected/><Panes><Pane><Number>3</Number><ActiveRow>24</ActiveRow><ActiveCol>4</ActiveCol></Pane></Panes><ProtectObjects>False</ProtectObjects><ProtectScenarios>False</ProtectScenarios></WorksheetOptions></Worksheet></Workbook>